The paper discusses the challenges and requirements for service orchestration in modern IT infrastructures, which involve fog/edge computing, function as a service, and programmable infrastructures. These technologies are related to distributed computing (cs.DC), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
